{
  "texts": [
    "Equation (1) calculates the percentage of an acid with respect to weight, and Eq.",
    "(2) measures it with respect to volume:",
    "where N, V, Eq.wt and W define the normality of titrant (usually NaOH), the volume of titrant, equivalent weight of the acid and mass of the fruit.",
    "where V 1 and V 2 symbolize titrant's volume and sample's volume, respectively.",
    "Apart from TA, the Brix-Acid ratio is a desired metric, often in preference over Brix or acid alone is and in some instances is considered an objective measurement that reflects the consumer acceptability (Tyl & Sadler, 2017)."
  ]
}